Sequence Information.Peptide Name: EtDef4 (E. tenax defensin 4, natural AMPs; insects, arthropods, invertebrates, animals;  UCSS1; more AMPs?)

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (73.2%) tofly defensin DLP4.Activity: Active against S. aureus ATCC 25923 and 33592 (MIC 16 µg/mL), L. monocytogenes DSM 20600 (MIC 16 µg/mL), M. luteus DSM 20030 (MIC 16 µg/mL), M. smegmatis ATCC 607 (MIC 32 µg/mL).
Literature Information.Author: Hirsch R, Wiesner J, Bauer A, Marker A, Vogel H, Hammann PE, Vilcinskas A. 2020
Literature Information.Title: Antimicrobial Peptides from Rat-Tailed Maggots of the Drone Fly Eristalis tenax Show Potent Activity against Multidrug-Resistant Gram-Negative Bacteria
